<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1594,1872]" box="[199,868,1630,1657]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,414,1630,1656]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Short description.</emphasis>
(See 
<bibRefCitation author="Daly, M." box="[478,611,1630,1656]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="377 - 390" refId="ref12886" refString="Daly, M. (2004 a) Anatomy and Taxonomy of three species of sea anemones (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Actiniidae) from the Gulf of California, including Isoaulactinia hespervolita Daly, n. sp. Pacific Science, 3, 377 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.1353 / psc. 2004.0030" type="journal article" year="2004">Daly 2004a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barragan, Y. &amp; Sanchez, C. &amp; Rodriguez, E." box="[622,856,1630,1657]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="501 - 549" refId="ref12499" refString="Barragan, Y., Sanchez, C. &amp; Rodriguez, E. (2019) First inventory of sea anemones (Cnidaria: Actiniaria) from La Paz Bay, southern Gulf of California (Mexico). Zootaxa, 4559 (3), 501 - 549. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4559.3.4" type="journal article" year="2019">
Barragán 
<emphasis box="[732,781,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1594,1872]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,388,1666,1692]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Natural history.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1869" box="[394,602,1666,1692]" class="Anthozoa" family="Actiniidae" genus="Anthopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="dowii">
<emphasis box="[394,602,1666,1692]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Anthopleura dowii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the intertidal zone, on boulders and in tide pools, and can be found in areas of high swell (
<bibRefCitation author="Daly, M." box="[405,542,1702,1728]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="377 - 390" refId="ref12886" refString="Daly, M. (2004 a) Anatomy and Taxonomy of three species of sea anemones (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Actiniidae) from the Gulf of California, including Isoaulactinia hespervolita Daly, n. sp. Pacific Science, 3, 377 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.1353 / psc. 2004.0030" type="journal article" year="2004">Daly 2004a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="156" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1594,1872]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1738,1764]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Distribution.</emphasis>
From Mexico to 
<collectingCountry box="[553,642,1739,1765]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="GBIF &amp; Global Biodiversity Information Facility, GBIF" box="[657,791,1738,1764]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" refId="ref14095" refString="GBIF (2021) Global Biodiversity Information Facility, GBIF Occurrences of Anthopleura dowii. Avalible https: // doi. org / 10.15468 / dl. fqxdhm (accessed 7 October 2021)" type="book" year="2021">GBIF 2021</bibRefCitation>
). This species has been previously reported in Mexico in Puerto Escondido, Cerritos, Tecolote and Caleritas, along the coast of Baja California Sur; and in Puerto Peñasco and San Carlos Bay, along the coast of Sonora (
<bibRefCitation author="Carlgren, O." box="[688,855,1810,1837]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="415 - 449" refId="ref12829" refString="Carlgren, O. (1951) The actinian fauna of the Gulf of California. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 101, 415 - 449." type="journal article" year="1951">Carlgren 1951</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Daly, M." box="[867,1000,1810,1836]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="377 - 390" refId="ref12886" refString="Daly, M. (2004 a) Anatomy and Taxonomy of three species of sea anemones (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Actiniidae) from the Gulf of California, including Isoaulactinia hespervolita Daly, n. sp. Pacific Science, 3, 377 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.1353 / psc. 2004.0030" type="journal article" year="2004">Daly 2004a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barragan, Y. &amp; Sanchez, C. &amp; Rodriguez, E." box="[1013,1248,1810,1837]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="501 - 549" refId="ref12499" refString="Barragan, Y., Sanchez, C. &amp; Rodriguez, E. (2019) First inventory of sea anemones (Cnidaria: Actiniaria) from La Paz Bay, southern Gulf of California (Mexico). Zootaxa, 4559 (3), 501 - 549. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4559.3.4" type="journal article" year="2019">
Barragán 
<emphasis box="[1123,1172,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record for El Conejo, in Baja California Sur.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
